cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the problem of statistical machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as Bayesian Optimization is used to tune the parameters. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine translation is a subfield of AI. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for machine translation, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as CNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Finally, the paper deals with optimization, which could place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
